WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:18.795 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.795 --> 00:00:20.670 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to Beyond Belief.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:23.400 align:middle line:10%
We've got an amazing
story for you tonight.

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:26.790 align:middle line:10%
As a teenager, Jason
Shurka endured--

00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:33.230 align:middle line:10%
get this-- 23 shoulder
dislocations, three surgeries,

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:35.760 align:middle line:10%
and a near leg amputation.

00:00:35.760 --> 00:00:38.790 align:middle line:84%
Drawing on the fundamental
laws of creation,

00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:42.840 align:middle line:84%
he transformed his life and now
inspires others to do the same.

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:47.180 align:middle line:10%
Founder of UNIFYD TV and
Unified Healing, his latest book

00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:49.740 align:middle line:10%
is called Accessing Awareness.

00:00:49.740 --> 00:00:51.960 align:middle line:84%
Jason, welcome back
to Beyond Belief.

00:00:51.960 --> 00:00:52.950 align:middle line:84%
JASON SHURKA: Thank
you very much, George.

00:00:52.950 --> 00:00:54.117 align:middle line:90%
It's great to see you again.

00:00:54.117 --> 00:00:57.840 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: 23 shoulder separations?

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:59.475 align:middle line:90%
How did that happen?

00:00:59.475 --> 00:01:00.350 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: It was a lot.

00:01:00.350 --> 00:01:01.940 align:middle line:90%
It started when I was 14.

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:05.660 align:middle line:84%
It happened between 14
and 18, 19 years old.

00:01:05.660 --> 00:01:07.250 align:middle line:90%
So about four to five years.

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:09.230 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Did you have an
accident or anything?

00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:10.030 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: No.

00:01:10.030 --> 00:01:12.620 align:middle line:10%
The first time, I went
to reach for something,

00:01:12.620 --> 00:01:14.720 align:middle line:10%
it spontaneously popped out.

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:17.900 align:middle line:10%
Never stopped, and it just
kept getting worse and worse.

00:01:17.900 --> 00:01:19.580 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, it would
happen in my sleep.

00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:21.050 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Does it still happen?

00:01:21.050 --> 00:01:22.240 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: No.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:24.550 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: What happened
to make it stop?

00:01:24.550 --> 00:01:26.870 align:middle line:10%
SHURKA: Well, if
you ask the doctors,

00:01:26.870 --> 00:01:28.240 align:middle line:10%
they'll tell you surgery.

00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:30.320 align:middle line:10%
But once wasn't enough.

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:31.310 align:middle line:10%
Twice wasn't enough.

00:01:31.310 --> 00:01:33.050 align:middle line:10%
The third one, I guess, was.

00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:36.830 align:middle line:84%
In my opinion, I see things
from a different perspective.

00:01:36.830 --> 00:01:40.010 align:middle line:84%
I believe that everything
happens for us, and not to us.

00:01:40.010 --> 00:01:42.160 align:middle line:84%
And when you learn the
lesson that something's

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:43.300 align:middle line:84%
trying to teach
you, it doesn't have

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:44.540 align:middle line:90%
to come back your way again.

00:01:44.540 --> 00:01:46.820 align:middle line:90%
So that's my way of seeing it.

00:01:46.820 --> 00:01:50.530 align:middle line:84%
The doctors may disagree,
but I understood over time--

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:52.480 align:middle line:84%
and I'm still understanding--
but I understood

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:54.230 align:middle line:90%
what it was trying to show me.

00:01:54.230 --> 00:01:56.210 align:middle line:90%
I acknowledged the lessons.

00:01:56.210 --> 00:01:58.320 align:middle line:84%
And why does it
have to happen again

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:00.610 align:middle line:84%
if you already got the gift
it was trying to give you?

00:02:00.610 --> 00:02:02.830 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Can you move your
arm without much pain?

00:02:02.830 --> 00:02:03.730 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Very much so.

00:02:03.730 --> 00:02:04.563 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Look at you.

00:02:04.563 --> 00:02:07.380 align:middle line:90%
You're doing better than me.

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:08.180 align:middle line:90%
Well, good for you.

00:02:08.180 --> 00:02:08.980 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Thank you.

00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:11.350 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: But this set you on
a spiritual path, didn't it?

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:12.150 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yeah.

00:02:12.150 --> 00:02:13.325 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Tell me about that.

00:02:13.325 --> 00:02:15.250 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: So you brought
up the leg amputation.

00:02:15.250 --> 00:02:18.790 align:middle line:84%
That's a big one because
that was the cherry on top.

00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:21.180 align:middle line:90%
So 14 years old, it started.

00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:24.930 align:middle line:90%
15, 16, 17, 18, 19.

00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:28.710 align:middle line:84%
On my 19th birthday, I was
in the hospital with a staph

00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:30.420 align:middle line:90%
infection in my left leg.

00:02:30.420 --> 00:02:33.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's a whole long
story in and of itself,

00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:36.970 align:middle line:84%
but I lost 25% of
my body weight.

00:02:36.970 --> 00:02:37.770 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: God.

00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:44.610 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: 19th birthday was there,
in dire need of as much support

00:02:44.610 --> 00:02:46.000 align:middle line:90%
as possible.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:47.260 align:middle line:90%
And it almost killed me.

00:02:47.260 --> 00:02:48.640 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't just a leg amputation.

00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:51.840 align:middle line:84%
I was about 24 hours away
from that hitting my blood

00:02:51.840 --> 00:02:54.040 align:middle line:90%
and it completely taking me out.

00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:56.080 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Almost like sepsis,
for crying out loud.

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:57.860 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: It was very, very bad.

00:02:57.860 --> 00:03:02.180 align:middle line:84%
So it was throughout that time
that really got me thinking.

00:03:02.180 --> 00:03:05.380 align:middle line:84%
It was the first time in my
life where I was laying down,

00:03:05.380 --> 00:03:07.970 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't have
a phone to look at,

00:03:07.970 --> 00:03:09.680 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't have a TV to watch.

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:11.830 align:middle line:84%
And it was the first
time where I woke up

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:14.780 align:middle line:84%
and I actually heard my
heartbeat for the first time.

00:03:14.780 --> 00:03:16.520 align:middle line:84%
Not just felt it,
but I heard it.

00:03:16.520 --> 00:03:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And I heard the
spaces in between.

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:22.390 align:middle line:84%
The moments of silence
and stillness in between.

00:03:22.390 --> 00:03:26.420 align:middle line:84%
And it got me thinking, where
does all of this come from?

00:03:26.420 --> 00:03:29.350 align:middle line:84%
Where does all action,
where does all life actually

00:03:29.350 --> 00:03:30.290 align:middle line:90%
emerge from?

00:03:30.290 --> 00:03:32.830 align:middle line:84%
And it really is in those
moments of presence,

00:03:32.830 --> 00:03:34.190 align:middle line:90%
and those moments of stillness.

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:38.650 align:middle line:84%
So that cherry on top was what
got me to start seeing things

00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:39.590 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:03:39.590 --> 00:03:43.550 align:middle line:84%
And it just started downloading
into me like a machine.

00:03:43.550 --> 00:03:44.990 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I
started reading,

00:03:44.990 --> 00:03:46.407 align:middle line:84%
and that's when I
started writing.

00:03:46.407 --> 00:03:48.640 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: How many books
did you start reading?

00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:49.550 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: A lot.

00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:52.620 align:middle line:84%
So up until 19, I never
read a book in my life.

00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:56.490 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why was because I
was like a normal kid in school,

00:03:56.490 --> 00:03:59.100 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't want to be
the weird one or the nerd,

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:01.050 align:middle line:90%
so I just kind of fit in.

00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:03.780 align:middle line:84%
Although, I was very
interested in things,

00:04:03.780 --> 00:04:06.873 align:middle line:84%
I just didn't want people to
look at me different because--

00:04:06.873 --> 00:04:09.540 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: You didn't want them to
know what you were doing, right?

00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:10.980 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yeah, kind of.

00:04:10.980 --> 00:04:13.730 align:middle line:84%
So I kind of sat there,
and for a long time,

00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:15.290 align:middle line:84%
I hid my true self
because I didn't

00:04:15.290 --> 00:04:18.089 align:middle line:84%
want to be looked at in
a weird way in school.

00:04:18.089 --> 00:04:20.459 align:middle line:84%
But 19, I picked
up my first book.

00:04:20.459 --> 00:04:24.110 align:middle line:84%
It was called The
One Minute Cure--

00:04:24.110 --> 00:04:25.920 align:middle line:90%
all about hydrogen peroxide.

00:04:25.920 --> 00:04:27.690 align:middle line:84%
It took me two or
three hours to read.

00:04:27.690 --> 00:04:29.880 align:middle line:84%
And the second one was
called Energy Medicine.

00:04:29.880 --> 00:04:34.970 align:middle line:84%
And I started getting into these
medical-but-spiritual aspects

00:04:34.970 --> 00:04:35.770 align:middle line:90%
of learning things.

00:04:35.770 --> 00:04:36.030 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Holistic.

00:04:36.030 --> 00:04:37.740 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Yeah,
holistic alternative.

00:04:37.740 --> 00:04:41.520 align:middle line:84%
And it brought me down this path
where it became this obsession.

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:43.700 align:middle line:84%
I read like 40, 42
books that year,

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:46.640 align:middle line:90%
and it started a beautiful path.

00:04:46.640 --> 00:04:49.350 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: That's more books than
most people read in a lifetime.

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:51.780 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: But it wasn't just
reading, it was studying.

00:04:51.780 --> 00:04:54.470 align:middle line:84%
You see, if you go back
to those books on my shelf

00:04:54.470 --> 00:04:58.030 align:middle line:84%
and you open them, it's
highlighting, it's taking notes,

00:04:58.030 --> 00:04:58.830 align:middle line:90%
it's studying.

00:04:58.830 --> 00:05:00.990 align:middle line:84%
That's how you become
the information,

00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:02.610 align:middle line:90%
not just learn the information.

00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:07.365 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Who have you learned
from in terms of teachers?

00:05:07.365 --> 00:05:08.990 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Quite honestly,
the people that

00:05:08.990 --> 00:05:10.470 align:middle line:90%
hurt me the most in my life.

00:05:10.470 --> 00:05:11.460 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Oh, really?

00:05:11.460 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yeah.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:14.150 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's not just me.

00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:17.972 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Without giving us names,
what kind of people hurt you?

00:05:17.972 --> 00:05:19.680 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: People that
stab you in the back.

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:21.330 align:middle line:84%
This is for everybody,
not just myself.

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:22.130 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Friends.

00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:27.030 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Friends, family
members, business partners.

00:05:27.030 --> 00:05:29.310 align:middle line:90%
I truly, truly believe--

00:05:29.310 --> 00:05:32.610 align:middle line:84%
as hard as it may be-- going
through those tough experiences,

00:05:32.610 --> 00:05:34.980 align:middle line:84%
those are the experiences
where you learn the most.

00:05:34.980 --> 00:05:37.430 align:middle line:84%
It's the experiences where
you gain the most, where

00:05:37.430 --> 00:05:38.610 align:middle line:90%
you get the strongest.

00:05:38.610 --> 00:05:43.100 align:middle line:84%
And although they're hard, if we
can find a way to embrace them,

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:45.770 align:middle line:84%
you become a completely
different and more evolved

00:05:45.770 --> 00:05:47.340 align:middle line:90%
person throughout those people.

00:05:47.340 --> 00:05:50.970 align:middle line:84%
So in a way, it's the
worst people in your life

00:05:50.970 --> 00:05:52.970 align:middle line:84%
that are really giving
you the greatest lessons.

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:54.690 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: You trusted
them, didn't you?

00:05:54.690 --> 00:05:55.490 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Big time.

00:05:55.490 --> 00:05:57.800 align:middle line:90%


00:05:57.800 --> 00:06:00.910 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: How many times
did they hurt you?

00:06:00.910 --> 00:06:04.510 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Well,
quite a few people.

00:06:04.510 --> 00:06:07.640 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:09.300 align:middle line:84%
They didn't hurt
me, they helped me.

00:06:09.300 --> 00:06:13.170 align:middle line:84%
And we have to clear that
up because it wasn't--

00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:16.110 align:middle line:84%
yes, on the surface, it's
individuals hurting you.

00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'd encourage
everybody that's

00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:20.745 align:middle line:84%
watching this right now, think
of those individuals that

00:06:20.745 --> 00:06:21.870 align:middle line:90%
have hurt you in your life.

00:06:21.870 --> 00:06:24.660 align:middle line:84%
Think of those individuals
that you've been wronged by,

00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.290 align:middle line:84%
and try to understand what
they've actually taught you

00:06:27.290 --> 00:06:28.410 align:middle line:90%
through that process.

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:31.020 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, on the
surface, they hurt me.

00:06:31.020 --> 00:06:34.027 align:middle line:84%
But at the core of it
all, they're my guides.

00:06:34.027 --> 00:06:34.860 align:middle line:90%
They're my teachers.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:36.570 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Do you deal
with them still?

00:06:36.570 --> 00:06:38.000 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Some.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.265 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Have you forgiven them?

00:06:40.265 --> 00:06:41.690 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Working on it.

00:06:41.690 --> 00:06:43.222 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: That's the hardest part.

00:06:43.222 --> 00:06:44.930 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: But it's the
most important part.

00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And I say "working
on it" and not "yes"

00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:49.170 align:middle line:84%
because I'm a human being
like everybody else.

00:06:49.170 --> 00:06:52.320 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's important
for us to relate to each other,

00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:55.920 align:middle line:84%
where you could be the greatest
guru and teacher out there.

00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:58.390 align:middle line:84%
We're all here to
learned something new.

00:06:58.390 --> 00:07:00.630 align:middle line:84%
We're all here to go
through experiences.

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:02.820 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Did you teach
yourself, Jason?

00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:07.890 align:middle line:90%
Or did these events teach you?

00:07:07.890 --> 00:07:09.390 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: That's a
beautiful question.

00:07:09.390 --> 00:07:13.520 align:middle line:84%
Well, every event,
every experience

00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:15.840 align:middle line:84%
has the ability to
teach us something,

00:07:15.840 --> 00:07:19.820 align:middle line:84%
but it's you as the
individual to make the choice,

00:07:19.820 --> 00:07:21.740 align:middle line:84%
through your own free
will, to be open enough

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:23.220 align:middle line:90%
to see it in that way.

00:07:23.220 --> 00:07:26.075 align:middle line:84%
So all the things that
happened to me in my life,

00:07:26.075 --> 00:07:27.950 align:middle line:84%
and all the things that
happened to all of us

00:07:27.950 --> 00:07:30.990 align:middle line:84%
throughout our lives, have
the ability to teach us.

00:07:30.990 --> 00:07:32.990 align:middle line:84%
It was that moment
in my life that

00:07:32.990 --> 00:07:36.120 align:middle line:84%
happened where I decided
to open up and say, OK,

00:07:36.120 --> 00:07:37.860 align:middle line:90%
what are you trying to show me?

00:07:37.860 --> 00:07:40.620 align:middle line:84%
So I would say it's a
combination of both.

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:42.420 align:middle line:84%
It's not so much
that I taught myself.

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:44.390 align:middle line:84%
It's that I was open
to the teachings that

00:07:44.390 --> 00:07:45.990 align:middle line:90%
were in front of me all along.

00:07:45.990 --> 00:07:49.770 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Tell us about the
fundamental laws of creation.

00:07:49.770 --> 00:07:51.720 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:58.330 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: So I'll go to Greek
mythology, Greek teachers,

00:07:58.330 --> 00:07:59.265 align:middle line:90%
ancient teachers.

00:07:59.265 --> 00:08:00.640 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: We're
going way back now.

00:08:00.640 --> 00:08:01.440 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yeah.

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:05.530 align:middle line:84%
There's a teacher, a
philosopher, named Parmenides.

00:08:05.530 --> 00:08:11.760 align:middle line:84%
Parmenides is famous for writing
two poems, The Way of Truth

00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:13.920 align:middle line:90%
and The Way of Opinion.

00:08:13.920 --> 00:08:16.980 align:middle line:84%
The Way of Opinion
is what most of us

00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:19.180 align:middle line:84%
live according to
today as human beings--

00:08:19.180 --> 00:08:20.410 align:middle line:90%
meaning, duality.

00:08:20.410 --> 00:08:23.730 align:middle line:90%
This and that, good and bad.

00:08:23.730 --> 00:08:28.320 align:middle line:84%
The Way of Truth
is what Parmenides

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:30.210 align:middle line:84%
would say the gods
live according to,

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:33.120 align:middle line:90%
which is singularity, oneness.

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:35.559 align:middle line:84%
Those are two completely
different worlds.

00:08:35.559 --> 00:08:38.912 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: You have learned
a lot, my friend.

00:08:38.912 --> 00:08:40.620 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: They're actually
very short poems

00:08:40.620 --> 00:08:42.287 align:middle line:84%
that you can study
yourself, but they're

00:08:42.287 --> 00:08:44.800 align:middle line:84%
profound in terms
of what they teach.

00:08:44.800 --> 00:08:49.330 align:middle line:84%
So these laws of creation
that we're talking about here

00:08:49.330 --> 00:08:52.100 align:middle line:84%
is based on his work,
many other people's work.

00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:54.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not original to me
in any way whatsoever,

00:08:54.740 --> 00:08:56.620 align:middle line:84%
but I kind put my
own twist on it

00:08:56.620 --> 00:09:00.550 align:middle line:84%
and said, OK, how can we not
just know this, but apply this

00:09:00.550 --> 00:09:02.085 align:middle line:90%
and live according to it?

00:09:02.085 --> 00:09:04.820 align:middle line:84%
Now, am I perfect and
applied every single day?

00:09:04.820 --> 00:09:06.230 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm a human being.

00:09:06.230 --> 00:09:09.910 align:middle line:84%
