00:28:47.040 --> 00:28:50.020 align:middle line:84%
because you are an
expression, or I should say,

00:28:50.020 --> 00:28:53.885 align:middle line:84%
your life is an expression
of your mind's program.

00:28:53.885 --> 00:28:56.070 align:middle line:84%
So we first have to
understand with this

00:28:56.070 --> 00:28:59.740 align:middle line:84%
that it is your mind's program
that makes up your life.

00:28:59.740 --> 00:29:02.200 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Do we start with
thought, belief in mind.

00:29:02.200 --> 00:29:04.080 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: So the
question is, how do we

00:29:04.080 --> 00:29:07.710 align:middle line:84%
reprogram the mind in
order to have a better

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:09.735 align:middle line:90%
expression of our lives?

00:29:09.735 --> 00:29:11.850 align:middle line:84%
It starts with a thought
and belief in your mind

00:29:11.850 --> 00:29:13.485 align:middle line:90%
as the first step.

00:29:13.485 --> 00:29:17.280 align:middle line:84%
It goes to step two, which is
the reflection of that thought

00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:18.280 align:middle line:90%
and belief in your mind.

00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:21.310 align:middle line:84%
So instead of just saying
words, let's give examples.

00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:26.830 align:middle line:84%
You may think I'm never
going to find the one.

00:29:26.830 --> 00:29:31.000 align:middle line:84%
And that thought is a
frequency from step one, which

00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:35.570 align:middle line:84%
will reflect in step two as, I'm
not finding that person for me,

00:29:35.570 --> 00:29:36.890 align:middle line:90%
I'm not finding my soulmate.

00:29:36.890 --> 00:29:39.958 align:middle line:90%
Why is this happening to me?

00:29:39.958 --> 00:29:41.500 align:middle line:84%
Step three is then
going to bring you

00:29:41.500 --> 00:29:44.380 align:middle line:84%
to analyzing the
programming of your mind

00:29:44.380 --> 00:29:45.710 align:middle line:90%
by observing your words.

00:29:45.710 --> 00:29:49.150 align:middle line:84%
So your mind's program is
made up of three things--

00:29:49.150 --> 00:29:51.760 align:middle line:90%
thought, belief, and words.

00:29:51.760 --> 00:29:55.540 align:middle line:84%
It's very hard to say change
your thought and belief,

00:29:55.540 --> 00:29:57.850 align:middle line:84%
but it's very easy
to say, pay attention

00:29:57.850 --> 00:30:00.760 align:middle line:84%
to your words, which are an
expression of your thought

00:30:00.760 --> 00:30:01.880 align:middle line:90%
and belief.

00:30:01.880 --> 00:30:04.780 align:middle line:84%
And when you can change your
words, which are made up

00:30:04.780 --> 00:30:08.680 align:middle line:84%
of frequencies, you then imprint
your thoughts and beliefs

00:30:08.680 --> 00:30:09.560 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:30:09.560 --> 00:30:11.420 align:middle line:90%
This is down to a science.

00:30:11.420 --> 00:30:14.900 align:middle line:84%
But to be able to understand
which words, you want to change,

00:30:14.900 --> 00:30:17.230 align:middle line:84%
in order to change
the program, you first

00:30:17.230 --> 00:30:22.230 align:middle line:84%
have to analyze them by
observing those words.

00:30:22.230 --> 00:30:25.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, you begin to use
specific words according

00:30:25.920 --> 00:30:28.470 align:middle line:84%
to specific formulas
that we can speak about,

00:30:28.470 --> 00:30:30.970 align:middle line:90%
to reprogram your mind.

00:30:30.970 --> 00:30:33.790 align:middle line:84%
There are certain words
that will hold you back.

00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:36.880 align:middle line:84%
There are certain words that
will propel you forward.

00:30:36.880 --> 00:30:39.120 align:middle line:84%
There are certain
words that will

00:30:39.120 --> 00:30:43.150 align:middle line:84%
create a positive and productive
imprint on your minds program.

00:30:43.150 --> 00:30:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And there are certain words
that will do the exact opposite.

00:30:46.360 --> 00:30:52.932 align:middle line:84%
For example, words
like will, want, not.

00:30:52.932 --> 00:30:53.860 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Should.

00:30:53.860 --> 00:30:54.790 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Should.

00:30:54.790 --> 00:30:56.110 align:middle line:90%
They're problematic.

00:30:56.110 --> 00:30:58.680 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: See, I have
picked up on you already.

00:30:58.680 --> 00:31:00.485 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: They're problematic.

00:31:00.485 --> 00:31:03.720 align:middle line:84%
So one of the main formulas
on here of understanding which

00:31:03.720 --> 00:31:07.530 align:middle line:84%
words to choose is based on,
what I like to call, the "I am"

00:31:07.530 --> 00:31:11.940 align:middle line:84%
formula based on
the acronym S-I-P.

00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:18.245 align:middle line:84%
The subject you focus on, the
implication of that subject,

00:31:18.245 --> 00:31:22.750 align:middle line:84%
and are you stating that
in the present tense.

00:31:22.750 --> 00:31:27.080 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to say I am,
but I'll give you an example.

00:31:27.080 --> 00:31:32.140 align:middle line:84%
If you say, I want
to be healthy,

00:31:32.140 --> 00:31:35.050 align:middle line:90%
or I don't want to be sick.

00:31:35.050 --> 00:31:38.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, you're focusing on
the wrong topic already.

00:31:38.030 --> 00:31:41.960 align:middle line:84%
And if you've focused on
the right subject and say,

00:31:41.960 --> 00:31:44.320 align:middle line:84%
I want to be healthy,
you're forgetting the fact

00:31:44.320 --> 00:31:46.640 align:middle line:84%
that you already have
that in your field.

00:31:46.640 --> 00:31:47.770 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to want it.

00:31:47.770 --> 00:31:49.480 align:middle line:90%
You need to access it right now.

00:31:49.480 --> 00:31:51.490 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: It's not what
God said to Moses--

00:31:51.490 --> 00:31:52.530 align:middle line:90%
I am.

00:31:52.530 --> 00:31:53.330 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: I am.

00:31:53.330 --> 00:31:56.510 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the most powerful
words, you can bring forth,

00:31:56.510 --> 00:31:59.660 align:middle line:84%
but it's the principles that
we're really working on.

00:31:59.660 --> 00:32:02.600 align:middle line:84%
For example, thank you for
blessing me with health.

00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:04.610 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
use the words I am.

00:32:04.610 --> 00:32:07.150 align:middle line:84%
But thank you for
blessing me with health

00:32:07.150 --> 00:32:10.370 align:middle line:84%
is using words to help
reprogram the mind.

00:32:10.370 --> 00:32:12.440 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that
over and over again,

00:32:12.440 --> 00:32:14.200 align:middle line:84%
you align with
different frequencies,

00:32:14.200 --> 00:32:17.240 align:middle line:84%
that impact your thoughts and
beliefs in a different way.

00:32:17.240 --> 00:32:20.740 align:middle line:84%
So that brings you to step
five, which is your new words,

00:32:20.740 --> 00:32:23.590 align:middle line:84%
become your new thoughts
and your new beliefs.

00:32:23.590 --> 00:32:25.650 align:middle line:84%
Your new thoughts
and your new beliefs

00:32:25.650 --> 00:32:29.140 align:middle line:84%
become that new minds program
because it's all energy.

00:32:29.140 --> 00:32:32.220 align:middle line:84%
Your new minds program
reflects your new life,

00:32:32.220 --> 00:32:35.130 align:middle line:90%
and it starts all over again.

00:32:35.130 --> 00:32:39.970 align:middle line:84%
It all comes down to you,
your thoughts, your beliefs,

00:32:39.970 --> 00:32:43.170 align:middle line:84%
and your words are
your greatest tool.

00:32:43.170 --> 00:32:46.540 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Did anybody teach you
this or did you experience it?

00:32:46.540 --> 00:32:48.180 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: I reverse
engineered what

00:32:48.180 --> 00:32:50.650 align:middle line:84%
I did in my life that
worked by chance,

00:32:50.650 --> 00:32:52.820 align:middle line:84%
and I understood
that it wasn't luck.

00:32:52.820 --> 00:32:53.620 align:middle line:90%
There was a reason.

00:32:53.620 --> 00:32:55.180 align:middle line:84%
That's the law of
cause and effect.

00:32:55.180 --> 00:32:58.453 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: How many people
cannot do what you did?

00:32:58.453 --> 00:32:59.620 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Everybody can do it.

00:32:59.620 --> 00:33:00.420 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: You sure?

00:33:00.420 --> 00:33:02.730 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: I'm positive.

00:33:02.730 --> 00:33:04.120 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: It's that easy?

00:33:04.120 --> 00:33:05.620 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Nobody said it's easy.

00:33:05.620 --> 00:33:07.980 align:middle line:84%
But if you put your
focus on something

00:33:07.980 --> 00:33:10.213 align:middle line:84%
and you want to get
somewhere, you will get there.

00:33:10.213 --> 00:33:12.130 align:middle line:84%
Now, I just want to make
something very clear.

00:33:12.130 --> 00:33:14.740 align:middle line:84%
You said how many
people can do it?

00:33:14.740 --> 00:33:17.990 align:middle line:84%
The very fact that I did it
means everybody can do it.

00:33:17.990 --> 00:33:22.460 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Yeah, but you were under
a crisis situation, weren't you?

00:33:22.460 --> 00:33:23.260 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yes.

00:33:23.260 --> 00:33:26.110 align:middle line:84%
But again, the
interconnectedness

00:33:26.110 --> 00:33:28.720 align:middle line:84%
of each and every one of
us, the experiences you

00:33:28.720 --> 00:33:31.550 align:middle line:90%
go through, teach me something.

00:33:31.550 --> 00:33:32.470 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:33:32.470 --> 00:33:34.990 align:middle line:84%
Because the experiences
you go through

00:33:34.990 --> 00:33:37.580 align:middle line:84%
allow you to evolve
in certain ways.

00:33:37.580 --> 00:33:38.930 align:middle line:90%
This is now the law of oneness.

00:33:38.930 --> 00:33:42.290 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Do we need
a crisis to react?

00:33:42.290 --> 00:33:43.090 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: No.

00:33:43.090 --> 00:33:45.440 align:middle line:90%
But they do help.

00:33:45.440 --> 00:33:46.940 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Makes it
easier, doesn't it?

00:33:46.940 --> 00:33:48.818 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: I mean, if
you're smooth sailing,

00:33:48.818 --> 00:33:50.360 align:middle line:84%
are you really going
to get stronger?

00:33:50.360 --> 00:33:52.480 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of a law
in and of itself.

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:53.480 align:middle line:90%
You're going to the gym.

00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:56.170 align:middle line:84%
Are you going to get stronger
muscles if you're not picking up

00:33:56.170 --> 00:33:57.550 align:middle line:90%
a weight?

00:33:57.550 --> 00:34:00.440 align:middle line:84%
The implication on the word
crisis is a negative thing.

00:34:00.440 --> 00:34:02.140 align:middle line:90%
I call them blessings.

00:34:02.140 --> 00:34:04.640 align:middle line:84%
We just need to change
our perspective on it.

00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:06.170 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Give us
an example, Jason,

00:34:06.170 --> 00:34:10.900 align:middle line:84%
of how you would utilize
this in your day to day life.

00:34:10.900 --> 00:34:14.739 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Every time something
negative happens to you

00:34:14.739 --> 00:34:16.290 align:middle line:90%
throughout the day.

00:34:16.290 --> 00:34:17.429 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Constantly.

00:34:17.429 --> 00:34:18.929 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Constantly.

00:34:18.929 --> 00:34:21.179 align:middle line:90%
You have a choice.

00:34:21.179 --> 00:34:24.810 align:middle line:84%
Not what happened
to you, but how

00:34:24.810 --> 00:34:27.750 align:middle line:84%
do you choose to respond to
it from the perspective of,

00:34:27.750 --> 00:34:29.500 align:middle line:90%
why is this happening for me?

00:34:29.500 --> 00:34:31.780 align:middle line:90%
So how do I actually apply this?

00:34:31.780 --> 00:34:34.510 align:middle line:84%
I change one word
in my sentence,

00:34:34.510 --> 00:34:36.600 align:middle line:84%
and in the very
beginning, I used

00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:39.969 align:middle line:84%
to put it in a reminder in my
phone every hour, every day,

00:34:39.969 --> 00:34:41.843 align:middle line:90%
until it became second nature.

00:34:41.843 --> 00:34:43.260 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
recommend people

00:34:43.260 --> 00:34:45.460 align:middle line:84%
do to make it become
second nature.

00:34:45.460 --> 00:34:47.969 align:middle line:90%
What is that one word?

00:34:47.969 --> 00:34:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Instead of, why is
this happening to me?

00:34:52.050 --> 00:34:56.744 align:middle line:84%
The "to" changes
to the word "for".

00:34:56.744 --> 00:34:59.285 align:middle line:90%
How is this happening for me?

00:34:59.285 --> 00:35:01.150 align:middle line:90%
Why is this happening for me?

00:35:01.150 --> 00:35:02.880 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: You turned
it into a positive.

00:35:02.880 --> 00:35:04.390 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Because
it is a positive.

00:35:04.390 --> 00:35:06.670 align:middle line:90%
Because-- back to Parmenides--

00:35:06.670 --> 00:35:10.620 align:middle line:84%
the way of truth
has no opposite.

00:35:10.620 --> 00:35:12.340 align:middle line:90%
Meaning, in that world--

00:35:12.340 --> 00:35:14.450 align:middle line:90%
the fundamental world of gods--

00:35:14.450 --> 00:35:17.600 align:middle line:90%
there is no good and bad.

00:35:17.600 --> 00:35:19.345 align:middle line:90%
There is good.

00:35:19.345 --> 00:35:22.400 align:middle line:84%
In the world of opinion,
there is good and bad.

00:35:22.400 --> 00:35:28.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, some may say, but
Jason, my son died.

00:35:28.750 --> 00:35:30.680 align:middle line:84%
How are you saying
that's a good thing?

00:35:30.680 --> 00:35:34.160 align:middle line:84%
How can you say that the loss
of a child is a good thing?

00:35:34.160 --> 00:35:35.650 align:middle line:90%
That's not what I'm saying.

00:35:35.650 --> 00:35:36.830 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: No, it's not.

00:35:36.830 --> 00:35:40.400 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: In the world
of physicality,

00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:42.865 align:middle line:90%
it's a horrible thing.

00:35:42.865 --> 00:35:45.410 align:middle line:84%
But pain and suffering
are two different things.

00:35:45.410 --> 00:35:49.120 align:middle line:84%
It's OK to be in pain of
the negative things that

00:35:49.120 --> 00:35:50.630 align:middle line:90%
happen in the physical world.

00:35:50.630 --> 00:35:56.475 align:middle line:84%
But suffering only exists when
you forget the way of truth,

00:35:56.475 --> 00:36:00.340 align:middle line:84%
because your son or your
daughter that you may have lost

00:36:00.340 --> 00:36:02.720 align:middle line:84%
has a soul that came
here with a purpose.

00:36:02.720 --> 00:36:06.350 align:middle line:84%
And you know that your soul
and their soul is intertwined,

00:36:06.350 --> 00:36:09.083 align:middle line:84%
and you know that everything
is happening for you.

00:36:09.083 --> 00:36:10.750 align:middle line:84%
And they came here
to teach you a lesson

00:36:10.750 --> 00:36:13.600 align:middle line:90%
and vice versa to help you grow.

00:36:13.600 --> 00:36:16.000 align:middle line:84%
And when you can see it
from that perspective.

00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:19.450 align:middle line:84%
You may be in pain, but
you don't have to suffer.

00:36:19.450 --> 00:36:20.950 align:middle line:90%
How do you apply it?

00:36:20.950 --> 00:36:24.600 align:middle line:84%
You remember every
second of every day.

00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:28.090 align:middle line:84%
Everything is happening
for me one way or another.

00:36:28.090 --> 00:36:30.900 align:middle line:84%
Now the question is,
where is the blessing?

00:36:30.900 --> 00:36:33.750 align:middle line:84%
When you look for
it, you will find it.

00:36:33.750 --> 00:36:35.710 align:middle line:84%
We have two aspects
to ourselves.

00:36:35.710 --> 00:36:37.830 align:middle line:84%
We have our higher
selves, and we have our--

00:36:37.830 --> 00:36:41.460 align:middle line:84%
us in our body
that we experience.

00:36:41.460 --> 00:36:45.540 align:middle line:84%
The higher self of yourself,
we call divine will.

00:36:45.540 --> 00:36:48.945 align:middle line:84%
You and your body,
we call free will.

00:36:48.945 --> 00:36:52.260 align:middle line:84%
They work together
constantly and the goal

00:36:52.260 --> 00:36:55.870 align:middle line:84%
is to align both if you want
to reach the highest levels.

00:36:55.870 --> 00:37:01.290 align:middle line:84%
Now, the analogy that I'll share
with you is driving in a car.

00:37:01.290 --> 00:37:06.510 align:middle line:84%
Let's say, you and me
represent the divine will

00:37:06.510 --> 00:37:08.780 align:middle line:84%
and the free will
of one individual.

00:37:08.780 --> 00:37:09.580 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: All right.

00:37:09.580 --> 00:37:11.350 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: You are the divine will.

00:37:11.350 --> 00:37:13.345 align:middle line:90%
I am the free will.

00:37:13.345 --> 00:37:16.135 align:middle line:84%
We're sitting in
a car right now.

00:37:16.135 --> 00:37:17.920 align:middle line:84%
You're on one side
with a steering wheel

00:37:17.920 --> 00:37:21.070 align:middle line:84%
and brakes and gas, and I'm on
the other side with a steering

00:37:21.070 --> 00:37:23.590 align:middle line:90%
wheel of brakes and gas.

00:37:23.590 --> 00:37:27.520 align:middle line:84%
And we know as the divine
will and the free will

00:37:27.520 --> 00:37:29.120 align:middle line:90%
where we each want to go.

00:37:29.120 --> 00:37:30.650 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Same car or two cars?

00:37:30.650 --> 00:37:31.460 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Same car.

00:37:31.460 --> 00:37:34.180 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact,
I'll make it simpler.

00:37:34.180 --> 00:37:38.170 align:middle line:84%
One car, two parts
of the same driver.

00:37:38.170 --> 00:37:39.590 align:middle line:90%
Divine will and free will.

00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:43.850 align:middle line:84%
Divine will knows the path and
the purpose of the higher self.

00:37:43.850 --> 00:37:47.230 align:middle line:84%
Free will does not, because
it came here to learn that.

00:37:47.230 --> 00:37:49.580 align:middle line:84%
But free will is
leading that car.

00:37:49.580 --> 00:37:52.600 align:middle line:84%
Until divine will
comes and intervenes.

00:37:52.600 --> 00:37:55.370 align:middle line:84%
So free will is driving,
driving, driving, driving.

00:37:55.370 --> 00:37:57.910 align:middle line:84%
Divine will is
there just in case.

00:37:57.910 --> 00:38:01.120 align:middle line:84%
And free will makes
a right turn, only

00:38:01.120 --> 00:38:03.880 align:middle line:84%
to forget that on the path
in the street that they're

00:38:03.880 --> 00:38:08.245 align:middle line:84%
driving on, there are trees
that it's about to crash into.

00:38:08.245 --> 00:38:11.325 align:middle line:84%
Divine will see that
because it can see ahead.

00:38:11.325 --> 00:38:14.560 align:middle line:84%
So it immediately jerks
the car back onto the road.

00:38:14.560 --> 00:38:16.590 align:middle line:84%
But free will doesn't
know that because it's

00:38:16.590 --> 00:38:19.140 align:middle line:84%
unaware of what
divine will is doing.

00:38:19.140 --> 00:38:22.470 align:middle line:84%
So what happens, free
will hits its head

00:38:22.470 --> 00:38:25.270 align:middle line:84%
against the wind,
the window, and says,

00:38:25.270 --> 00:38:27.060 align:middle line:90%
why is this happening to me?

00:38:27.060 --> 00:38:30.660 align:middle line:84%
But if free will was
aware of divine will,

00:38:30.660 --> 00:38:33.030 align:middle line:84%
it would have understood
that divine will is

00:38:33.030 --> 00:38:37.690 align:middle line:84%
doing its best to save its
life and to keep it on track.

00:38:37.690 --> 00:38:40.725 align:middle line:84%
That's what hardships
in our lives are.

00:38:40.725 --> 00:38:43.240 align:middle line:84%
It's us in the driver's
seat of free will,

00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:46.300 align:middle line:84%
with the partition between
us not seeing divine will,

00:38:46.300 --> 00:38:48.390 align:middle line:84%
forgetting that
everything is happening

00:38:48.390 --> 00:38:50.290 align:middle line:90%
for us to keep us on track.

00:38:50.290 --> 00:38:54.060 align:middle line:84%
It's all about free will
realigning itself right back

00:38:54.060 --> 00:38:55.210 align:middle line:90%
onto that road.

00:38:55.210 --> 00:38:57.700 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes we may
not be aware of it,

00:38:57.700 --> 00:39:01.170 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes we need to get
hit in order to wake up, which

00:39:01.170 --> 00:39:02.740 align:middle line:90%
goes back to the crisis.

00:39:02.740 --> 00:39:04.360 align:middle line:90%
We call it a crisis.

00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:05.890 align:middle line:90%
We call it a bad thing.

00:39:05.890 --> 00:39:08.100 align:middle line:84%
But it's that very
thing that saved you

00:39:08.100 --> 00:39:10.693 align:middle line:84%
from driving and crashing
straight into that tree that

00:39:10.693 --> 00:39:11.610 align:middle line:90%
would have killed you.

00:39:11.610 --> 00:39:15.110 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Who can get you back
on that path of righteousness?

00:39:15.110 --> 00:39:17.210 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Yourself
will always try to.

00:39:17.210 --> 00:39:18.840 align:middle line:90%
Now, call it divine will.

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:20.320 align:middle line:90%
Call it divine consciousness.

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:21.120 align:middle line:90%
Call it God.

00:39:21.120 --> 00:39:22.410 align:middle line:90%
Call it whatever you want.

00:39:22.410 --> 00:39:23.910 align:middle line:90%
I don't care what you call it.

00:39:23.910 --> 00:39:27.810 align:middle line:84%
You will always be brought
back onto that path,

00:39:27.810 --> 00:39:32.100 align:middle line:84%
unless you continuously choose
not to go back onto that path.

00:39:32.100 --> 00:39:35.130 align:middle line:84%
At which point, if you do
that over and over again,

00:39:35.130 --> 00:39:37.290 align:middle line:84%
you have no reason
to be here anymore.

00:39:37.290 --> 00:39:39.720 align:middle line:84%
You move on come
back, you try again.

00:39:39.720 --> 00:39:42.840 align:middle line:84%
We call that reincarnation
the evolution process.

00:39:42.840 --> 00:39:45.595 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Why would we
want to come back?

00:39:45.595 --> 00:39:47.580 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: Well, you
may not as George,

00:39:47.580 --> 00:39:49.320 align:middle line:84%
but your soul most
definitely does,

00:39:49.320 --> 00:39:51.810 align:middle line:84%
because the goal of
the soul is to learn.

00:39:51.810 --> 00:39:54.320 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: I want to come
back as Jason Shurka.

00:39:54.320 --> 00:39:58.010 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: I want to
come back as highly

00:39:58.010 --> 00:39:59.760 align:middle line:90%
evolved as you possibly can.

00:39:59.760 --> 00:40:03.210 align:middle line:84%
But to do that, we need to
go through those hard times.

00:40:03.210 --> 00:40:05.820 align:middle line:84%
And they're not meant to
bog you down and hurt you.

00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:07.515 align:middle line:90%
They're meant to teach you.

00:40:07.515 --> 00:40:09.030 align:middle line:84%
And again, we get
caught up in them.

00:40:09.030 --> 00:40:10.030 align:middle line:90%
I get caught up in them.

00:40:10.030 --> 00:40:11.285 align:middle line:90%
We all do.

00:40:11.285 --> 00:40:13.390 align:middle line:84%
But they're not there
to take you out.

00:40:13.390 --> 00:40:15.810 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: How often do
you manifest things?

00:40:15.810 --> 00:40:17.830 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: We all manifest
things all the time.

00:40:17.830 --> 00:40:18.990 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Constantly?

00:40:18.990 --> 00:40:20.600 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: That's creation.

00:40:20.600 --> 00:40:21.970 align:middle line:90%
That's accession.

00:40:21.970 --> 00:40:24.075 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
doing all the time.

00:40:24.075 --> 00:40:25.890 align:middle line:84%
How often do I do
it consciously,

00:40:25.890 --> 00:40:27.340 align:middle line:90%
is a whole different story.

00:40:27.340 --> 00:40:28.960 align:middle line:90%
Because there's manifestation.

00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
conscious manifestation.

00:40:32.190 --> 00:40:33.340 align:middle line:90%
I do it pretty often.

00:40:33.340 --> 00:40:37.120 align:middle line:84%
Every single morning I sit
down, I meditate, I pray, I ask,

00:40:37.120 --> 00:40:39.250 align:middle line:90%
I thank, and I move on.

00:40:39.250 --> 00:40:41.890 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: What is SIP formula.

00:40:41.890 --> 00:40:43.780 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: That is
the "I am" formula.

00:40:43.780 --> 00:40:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Subject, implication,
present tense.

00:40:46.390 --> 00:40:49.170 align:middle line:84%
The subject you focus
on must be the subject

00:40:49.170 --> 00:40:52.540 align:middle line:84%
that you want to access,
want to experience.

00:40:52.540 --> 00:40:56.560 align:middle line:84%
The implication of that
subject must be not,

00:40:56.560 --> 00:40:59.440 align:middle line:90%
will, want, or don't have.

00:40:59.440 --> 00:41:02.910 align:middle line:84%
But thank you for already
providing it to me.

00:41:02.910 --> 00:41:06.660 align:middle line:84%
And present tense is stating
it in the present tense.

00:41:06.660 --> 00:41:10.250 align:middle line:84%
So, so long as your intention
is expressed according to that

00:41:10.250 --> 00:41:13.170 align:middle line:84%
acronym, which is
that "I am" formula.

00:41:13.170 --> 00:41:16.910 align:middle line:84%
Subject, positive
focus, implication

00:41:16.910 --> 00:41:19.650 align:middle line:84%
of that subject,
and present tense,

00:41:19.650 --> 00:41:21.230 align:middle line:84%
it will make it a
whole lot easier

00:41:21.230 --> 00:41:23.790 align:middle line:84%
to be able to
consciously manifest.

00:41:23.790 --> 00:41:25.950 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: What is IBV formula?

00:41:25.950 --> 00:41:30.240 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: IBV is making the "I
am" formula 10 times stronger.

00:41:30.240 --> 00:41:33.300 align:middle line:90%
Intent, belief, visualization.

00:41:33.300 --> 00:41:37.190 align:middle line:84%
Your intent must be aligned
with the "I am" formula--

00:41:37.190 --> 00:41:40.385 align:middle line:84%
your subject, your implication,
your present tense.

00:41:40.385 --> 00:41:44.180 align:middle line:84%
Your belief must be
undoubted because it's

00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:47.190 align:middle line:84%
one thing to have a
belief and say, maybe,

00:41:47.190 --> 00:41:48.780 align:middle line:84%
but it's kind of
hard, I don't know.

00:41:48.780 --> 00:41:50.988 align:middle line:84%
That's already going to
align yourself with something

00:41:50.988 --> 00:41:53.300 align:middle line:84%
you may not be able to
access, something you may not

00:41:53.300 --> 00:41:54.390 align:middle line:90%
be able to experience.

00:41:54.390 --> 00:41:56.810 align:middle line:84%
So your belief
must be undoubted,

00:41:56.810 --> 00:41:59.700 align:middle line:84%
and your visualization
must be crystal clear.

00:41:59.700 --> 00:42:01.890 align:middle line:84%
And there's a way to play
between both of those,

00:42:01.890 --> 00:42:05.860 align:middle line:84%
because for some, it's hard to
be able to believe something,

00:42:05.860 --> 00:42:08.080 align:middle line:84%
but it's easier to
be able to see it.

00:42:08.080 --> 00:42:11.260 align:middle line:84%
And for others, it's hard
to be able to see something,

00:42:11.260 --> 00:42:13.630 align:middle line:84%
but it's easy to be
able to believe it.

00:42:13.630 --> 00:42:16.020 align:middle line:84%
If you can hone in
on one, the other one

00:42:16.020 --> 00:42:17.880 align:middle line:90%
will be a whole lot easier.

00:42:17.880 --> 00:42:20.430 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Jason, when you
were going through these 23

00:42:20.430 --> 00:42:23.160 align:middle line:84%
separations of your
shoulder, the three

00:42:23.160 --> 00:42:29.085 align:middle line:84%
surgeries, the possible leg
amputation, did you cry?

00:42:29.085 --> 00:42:30.720 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Every day.

00:42:30.720 --> 00:42:32.550 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: What was that like?

00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:33.540 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Horrible.

00:42:33.540 --> 00:42:36.010 align:middle line:84%
And yet amazing at the
same time, every day.

00:42:36.010 --> 00:42:38.020 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Was it a living hell?

00:42:38.020 --> 00:42:38.820 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Yes.

00:42:38.820 --> 00:42:40.090 align:middle line:90%
That brought me to heaven.

00:42:40.090 --> 00:42:41.923 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: Did that get
you on the right track?

00:42:41.923 --> 00:42:44.770 align:middle line:90%


00:42:44.770 --> 00:42:45.570 align:middle line:90%
SHURKA: Of course.

00:42:45.570 --> 00:42:48.780 align:middle line:90%


00:42:48.780 --> 00:42:49.630 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:42:49.630 --> 00:42:51.427 align:middle line:90%
GEORGE: Truly remarkable.

00:42:51.427 --> 00:42:54.010 align:middle line:84%
SHURKA: I think there's a lesson
there for all of us to learn,

00:42:54.010 --> 00:42:54.820 align:middle line:90%
which is important.

00:42:54.820 --> 00:42:57.585 align:middle line:84%
And I know that everybody
watching this right now

00:42:57.585 --> 00:43:00.990 align:middle line:84%
has something that they're
going through in their lives.

00:43:00.990 --> 00:43:03.030 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is there to hurt you.

00:43:03.030 --> 00:43:07.290 align:middle line:84%
Because if everything is
one and interconnected,

00:43:07.290 --> 00:43:11.270 align:middle line:84%
oneness source will never do
anything to hurt itself, ever.

00:43:11.270 --> 00:43:13.620 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, we
have to ask ourselves,

00:43:13.620 --> 00:43:17.460 align:middle line:84%
how is source trying to help
us right now in this hard time?

00:43:17.460 --> 00:43:19.230 align:middle line:84%
GEORGE: What's the
best advice, Jason,

00:43:19.230 --> 00:43:21.620 align:middle line:84%
you could give to
somebody who is going

00:43:21.620 --> 00:43:25.130 align:middle line:90%
through what you went through?

00:43:25.130 --> 00:43:26.900 align:middle line:10%
SHURKA: I am not
special in everybody's

00:43:26.900 --> 00:43:30.770 align:middle line:10%
gone through what I've gone
through in their own way.

00:43:30.770 --> 00:43:33.410 align:middle line:10%
Look for the hardest
things that have ever

00:43:33.410 --> 00:43:34.830 align:middle line:10%
happened to you in your life.

00:43:34.830 --> 00:43:38.240 align:middle line:84%
Focus on the people that are
the hardest people for you

00:43:38.240 --> 00:43:40.400 align:middle line:90%
to deal with in your life.

00:43:40.400 --> 00:43:43.640 align:middle line:84%
See them from a
lens of compassion.

00:43:43.640 --> 00:43:46.740 align:middle line:10%
See them from a lens
of understanding,

00:43:46.740 --> 00:43:48.830 align:middle line:10%
even though it's
difficult to understand.

00:43:48.830 --> 00:43:51.475 align:middle line:84%
And remember-- and this
is the biggest one--

00:43:51.475 --> 00:43:55.550 align:middle line:84%
never take anything
personally, ever.

00:43:55.550 --> 00:43:58.730 align:middle line:84%
If you can live according
to those very, very

00:43:58.730 --> 00:44:01.680 align:middle line:84%
simple little things
throughout your life,

00:44:01.680 --> 00:44:05.700 align:middle line:84%
specifically with never
taking anything personally,

00:44:05.700 --> 00:44:07.740 align:middle line:84%
you'll see people in
a whole different way

00:44:07.740 --> 00:44:10.660 align:middle line:84%
because that everybody's
just trying to do their best,

00:44:10.660 --> 00:44:14.140 align:middle line:84%
even if it seems hard,
even if it looks bad.

00:44:14.140 --> 00:44:18.670 align:middle line:84%
Everybody is doing their best
and with love, with compassion,

00:44:18.670 --> 00:44:21.450 align:middle line:84%
with forgiveness,
you can overcome

00:44:21.450 --> 00:44:22.990 align:middle line:90%
any obstacle in the world.

